# Generated from: specs/feature-umbrella-deliver-blender-mcp-only-recipe-asset-generation/requirements.md
# Issue: #27

Feature: Blender MCP-only recipe asset generation umbrella
  As an internal NMG game developer
  I want Blender MCP-only recipe asset generation coordinated as a multi-PR v1 feature
  So that supported asset families are generated locally with deterministic recipes, review gates, provenance, and Desktop/Mobile variants

  Background:
    Given the accepted ADR from issue #5 selects Blender MCP recipe generation for v1
    And the pinned Blender MCP host is the only active generation backend for supported v1 families

  Scenario: Blender MCP-only happy path
    Given a supported v1 asset request for a recipe family
    When nmg-game-dev runs the asset-generation happy path
    Then generation is performed through local Blender MCP recipe execution
    And no model server, hosted generation API, paid provider, quota-limited backend, Meshy, Hyper3D, Hunyuan3D, FLUX, ComfyUI, Diffusers, Substance, Material Maker, Mixamo, or CUDA-only path is invoked
    And the artifact provenance records a Blender recipe source

  Scenario: Multi-PR child delivery remains traceable
    Given umbrella issue #27 and the accepted ADR from issue #5
    When child issues #31, #35, #29, #33, #32, and #30 are implemented across separate PRs
    Then each child links back to the umbrella spec and ADR
    And each child remains independently reviewable
    And no child claims unrelated recipe, material, rigging, cleanup, or review-gate work is complete

  Scenario: Recipe jobs are orchestrated with provenance
    Given a pipeline stage requests a recipe-backed asset generation job
    When the job is submitted, polled, cancelled, completed, cached, or retried after a listener restart
    Then structured job status, progress, cancellation state, cache keys, artifact manifests, local output paths, recipe provenance, material provenance, Blender version, MCP version, and review artifact references are recorded in serializable sidecars
    And the job can be safely resumed or diagnosed from those sidecars

  Scenario: Supported recipe families produce reviewable GLBs
    Given a supported recipe family request with recipe id, seed, dimensions, style preset, and material preset
    When the recipe engine runs with deterministic inputs
    Then it emits Blender output, GLB export, object statistics, material statistics, polygon statistics, dimensions, and five-angle review renders
    And unsupported families fail with structured remediation instead of falling back to a provider backend

  Scenario: Materials and PBR packaging are Blender-owned
    Given a generated mesh from the recipe engine
    When the material and texture stage runs
    Then Blender procedural material assignment, UV unwrap, bake-down, GLB export, and PBR channel validation replace the current texture placeholder
    And no external texture generation backend is required
    And the sidecar records material preset provenance and PBR channel evidence

  Scenario: Cleanup, LOD, and variants are physical outputs
    Given a generated and textured asset
    When Blender cleanup, remesh, LOD, texture bake-down, and variant operators run
    Then Desktop and Mobile outputs are separate physical assets with identical logical names under their variant directories
    And sidecars record poly counts, texture byte totals, LOD levels, bake settings, and applied mobile budget values

  Scenario: Review gates block bad assets
    Given generated output with missing PBR channels, empty geometry, invalid scale, incoherent recipe geometry, over-budget Mobile variants, or an unsupported recipe-family request
    When inspection and review gates run
    Then review artifacts and budget reports are written
    And the workflow stops before UE import
    And the failure includes structured remediation suitable for rerun or backlog creation

  Scenario: Broad recipe catalog covers normal game asset, character, vehicle, and street-infrastructure needs
    Given the v1 recipe catalog is considered ready for normal NMG game production
    When catalog coverage tests run
    Then representative asset, character, creature, vehicle, road, streetlight, sign, and street-fixture recipes produce reviewable GLBs
    And each recipe family has a fixture spec, review bundle, sidecar provenance, and deterministic rerun coverage

  Scenario: Prompt-driven refinement improves models and textures inside the recipe workflow
    Given a generated recipe asset and a developer prompt requesting supported model or material changes
    When the refinement workflow runs
    Then supported prompt details map to deterministic recipe and material parameters
    And the rerun records refinement prompt, changed parameters, generated output, review bundle, and accepted or rejected state
    And unsupported prompt details fail without leaving the Blender MCP recipe workflow
